9f28fae4-82d9-43b8-9db1-81187a0f5dd2.10f15f29-57d2-4c51-94c1-bb4b317864e9.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

9f28fae4-82d9-43b8-9db1-81187a0f5dd2.a82f180b-b424-44cd-a0f6-61f3a5d37a98.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. 9f28fae4-82d9-43b8-9db1-81187a0f5dd2.aac3f767-8742-435e-8b7c-9fcdc04e9df3.transition.description=${header}

Inputs\: table - The tale to analyze. rowDelimiter - A delimiter that separates rows in the table. columnDelimiter - A delimiter that separates columns in the table. header-A columnDelimiter separated list of The names of columns. rowNames - The name of each row of data. Returns\: An html formatted statisticall analysis of the table. ExtraResults\: means - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column means. medians - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column medians. stddevs - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column standard deviations. zValues - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column z values. Responses\: success - the operation completed successfully. failure - failed to process the list or something went wrong. 9f28fae4-82d9-43b8-9db1-81187a0f5dd2.c609fa8b-a186-4634-8d35-645ef0e7ca4f.transition.description=outliers found. Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 9f28fae4-82d9-43b8-9db1-81187a0f5dd2.d35e6d60-1cb6-4490-a71f-2bb758e71b02.transition.description=no outlier found results\: ${output} 9f28fae4-82d9-43b8-9db1-81187a0f5dd2.d702d396-28e4-48db-8035-f8465ae8da9f.prompt=Notification method 9f28fae4-82d9-43b8-9db1-81187a0f5dd2.description=
Compares the loads of a list of windows servers. Useful for checking windows cluster load balancing.

Inputs\:
hosts - hosts to check.
delimiter - delimiter for hosts.
username - username for hosts.
password - password for hosts.
notifyMethod - How to report gathered information.

Returns\:
An html report.

Responses\:
success - no problems found.
diagnosed - potential problems found.
failure - something went wrong.
